The paper deals with the problem of clustering in graph metrics, which is a fundamental problem in data analysis and has applications in road networks and data visualization. The paper proposes a near-linear time construction of a coreset for $(k, z)$-Clustering in a graph $G$ whose treewidth is $\mathrm{tw}(G)$, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the shattering dimension and provides a bound on it, which is a concept from statistical learning theory, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with clustering, which is a problem in data mining, making cs.DM (Data Mining) a likely sub-category as well.
